        <num>CC 47</num>
        <heading>ABSENT PERSONS</heading>
        <content>
          <p>TITLE III.  ABSENT PERSONS
CHAPTER 1.  CURATORSHIP OF THE PROPERTY OF
ABSENT PERSONS
Art. 47.  Curator of an absent person's property
An absent person is one who has no representative in this state and whose whereabouts are not known and cannot be ascertained by diligent effort.
When an absent person owns property in this state, the court may, upon petition of any interested party and a showing of necessity, appoint a curator to manage the property of the absent person.</p>
        </content>
